      "message": "\u003e This was wtf for me. Apparently !\u003cbool alias\u003e has type \u003cbool alias\u003e and \"bool || \u003cbool alias\u003e\" doesn\u0027t work.\n\u003e \n\nMeaning that you get a compile error? This sort-of makes sense...\n\n\u003e Even more bizarrely:\n\u003e \n\u003e switch {\n\u003e case \u003cbool\u003e:\n\u003e   ...\n\u003e case \u003cbool alias\u003e:\n\u003e   ...\n\u003e }\n\u003e \n\u003e also doesn\u0027t work.\n\nWhat do you mean by that? Doesn\u0027t compile because the implicit comparison value of switch is `bool(true)` and so there\u0027s a type mismatch as well?\n\n\u003e \n\u003e But\n\u003e \n\u003e switch {\n\u003e case \u003cbool alias\u003e:\n\u003e   ...\n\u003e }\n\u003e \n\u003e does.\n\nOk, that\u0027s weird O_o",
